Plot Summary for 
The Texas Chain Saw Massacre (1974) 
En route to visit their grandfather&#039;s grave (which has apparently been ritualistically desecrated), five teenagers drive past a slaughterhouse, pick up (and quickly drop) a sinister hitch-hiker, eat some delicious home-cured meat at a roadside gas station, before ending up at the old family home... where they&#039;re plunged into a never-ending nightmare as they meet a family of cannibals who more than make up in power tools what they lack in social skills...
